Commentary Text: M Theekshana to Pollard, out Caught by Shivam Dube!! Huge strike for CSK and their ploy off using the spinner against KP has worked. That was a flattish carrom ball, Pollard looked to go aerial and found the hands of Dube in the deep. Those were nervous tentacles grabbing that delivery. Big strike for CSK in the context of the game. This was an encore of the 2010 IPL final. That straightish fielder. That Dhoni plot has had Pollard trapped again. Somethings don't change. Commentary Text: Santner to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Mukesh Choudhary!! This is a huge wicket for Chennai. Rohit has a grimace on his face. Suryakumar was itching to have a go and he opts for the sweep, moves across and sits down to play the shot, but Santner is a smart operator and just held the length back which did not allow Suryakumar to get under the shot, struck it flat and straight to long leg. Mukesh hangs on to a good catch and is now involved in all four dismissals. Suryakumar Yadav c Mukesh Choudhary b Santner 32(21) [4s-3 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Daniel Sams to Rayudu, out Caught by Pollard!! Picks out long-off this time! Rayudu's extremely up-and-down innings is cut short by a fine diving catch from Pollard at long-off. Sams can do no wrong with the ball. This is a full toss, there to be put away but Rayudu can't get hold of it. MI are hanging in there and fighting really hard. Sams with his third of the night, gets the in-angler to straighten just a fraction, Dube went hard on the drive with no footwork and the result was a healthy edge. Commentary Text: Unadkat to Uthappa, out Caught by Brevis!! Unadkat strikes! Those off-cutters of his are working well on this pitch, forced Uthappa to go across the line for the pull stroke but it wasn't a full-blooded shot at all.
